main event: A witness reported seeing a whitish object about 30-38 feet long with rotating white lights on the front and back over Los Angeles, California.
interesting points: The object hovered and then suddenly shot up and out of sight.
The object made no sound when it moved.
The witness was unable to provide the exact time of the sighting or the duration.
The report was lacking some key details requested on the questionnaire, such as the object's altitude, direction of travel, and the witness's emotional state.
The Air Force responded that the information provided was insufficient for a scientific evaluation.
